OL,3,CAir traffic control engineers working
OL,4,Cfrom home during meltdown - report
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FMany affected passengers were required
OL,8,Fto pay up front for alternative
OL,9,Fflights, food and accommodation ` and
OL,10,Fsubmitted claims to airlines for
OL,11,Freimbursement ` despite the carriers
OL,12,Fbeing legally required to provide
OL,13,Fthese.
OL,15,FThe inquiry panel found evidence of
OL,16,F"misinformation about passenger
OL,17,Frights", with leaflets handed out by
OL,18,Fsome airlines claiming passengers "had
OL,19,Fto make their own plans to get home".
